**Budget Analysis (Mid-Range $77K):**

| Category | Amount | Percentage | Rationale |
|----------|--------|------------|----------|
| **Projector** | $30,000 | 39.0% | Largest single expense; 2027 flagship model |
| **Speakers** | $9,500 | 12.3% | DIYSG reference-level (LCR, surrounds, Atmos) |
| **Main Electronics** | $9,700 | 12.6% | Marantz AV10, Buckeye amplification |
| **Subwoofer Electronics** | $4,400 | 5.7% | PURIFI monoblocks (silent, reference-grade) |
| **Acoustic Treatment** | $5,500 | 7.1% | DIY materials (OC 703, Roxul, Guilford fabric) |
| **Seating** | $6,000 | 7.8% | 2× 11-foot couches with Crowson prep |
| **Subwoofer System** | $3,600 | 4.7% | 8× UM18-22 drivers + enclosures |
| **Screen** | $3,000 | 3.9% | 170" 2.35:1 acoustically transparent |
| **Crowson Tactile** | $2,200 | 2.9% | 6× transducers + amplification |
| **Riser Platform** | $1,700 | 2.2% | CLD construction, isolation |
| **Equipment Rack** | $690 | 0.9% | 42U open-frame + access panel |
| **Stage Platform** | $540 | 0.7% | Three-zone construction |
| **Rear Wall System** | $370 | 0.5% | Backrest + AT panels |
| **TOTAL** | **$77,000** | **100%** | Mid-range estimate |

**Key Insights:**

1. **Projector Dominates (39%)**
   - Flagship model for 15-foot throw distance
   - JVC NZ or Sony XW7000ES class
   - Technology will advance significantly by 2027
   - Budget reassessment recommended closer to build

2. **Speakers + Electronics (25%)**
   - Combined $19,200 for all amplification and speakers
   - DIYSG provides reference performance at DIY pricing
   - Buckeye/PURIFI amplification = professional-grade sound
   - No compromises anywhere in signal chain

3. **Subwoofer System (10.4% total)**
   - $3,600 drivers/enclosures + $4,400 electronics = $8,000
   - Achieves 109 dB @ 20Hz (exceeds THX Reference)
   - PURIFI monoblocks = silent, state-of-the-art
   - Proper engineering vs. buying commercial subs

4. **Room Treatment (7.1%)**
   - DIY construction at material cost
   - Professional installation would be $15K-25K
   - Builder has expertise (saves $10K-18K in labor)
   - Critical for reference-level performance

5. **Platforms & Infrastructure (3.4%)**
   - Stage + Riser + Rack + Rear Wall = $2,610
   - Enables optimal component placement
   - CLD construction eliminates resonance
   - Professional appearance, DIY cost

**Value Proposition:**

**What You Get for $75K-95K:**
- Reference-level performance across all frequencies
- 109 dB @ 20Hz subwoofer capability (+4 dB over THX)
- 107-108 dB Atmos capability (+2-3 dB over THX)
- Silent operation (fanless PURIFI amplification)
- Professional cinema aesthetic
- Dirac Live + ART room correction
- 15-20+ year component lifespan
- True content ownership (no DRM/subscriptions)

**Commercial Equivalent:**
- Professional theater installation: $150K-250K
- Your cost: $75K-95K (50-65% savings)
- Advantage: DIY labor on construction/treatment
- Advantage: Component selection optimization
- Advantage: No contractor markup

**Where Money is Saved:**
- DIY construction (stage, riser, treatment)
- DIY speaker kits vs. commercial equivalents
- Direct amplifier purchase (Buckeye vs. retail)
- Own existing tools and skillset
- Network storage already in place

**Where Money is NOT Saved (Proper Investment):**
- Projector (flagship model essential)
- Marantz AV10 (Dirac Live + ART mandatory)
- PURIFI amplification (silent operation critical)
- Quality drivers (UM18-22, DIYSG speakers)
- Professional calibration ($500-1,500)

**Budget Flexibility:**
- **Minimum viable ($68,676):** Entry projector, minimal treatment
- **Recommended ($75,000-85,000):** Balanced across all categories
- **Maximum ($95,044):** Premium projector, extensive treatment, premium seating
- **Sweet spot ($80,000):** Excellent projector, comprehensive treatment, quality seating

**2027 Reassessment Strategy:**
1. Lock in projector budget closer to build (technology advancing)
2. Monitor DIYSG pricing (unlikely to change significantly)
3. Consider sales on Buckeye amplification
4. Source acoustic materials in bulk
5. Maintain 10% contingency for unforeseen expenses

---

**Summary by Category:**
- Front stage platform: $520-556 (includes larger corner pockets)
- Front subwoofer system (with 3" recessed drivers & integrated AT covers): $1,821
- Rear subwoofer system (with 3" recessed drivers & integrated AT covers): $1,786
- Subwoofer electronics (PURIFI amps, DSP): $4,200-4,600
- Equipment rack (including access panel): $640-740
- Riser platform: $1,593-1,798
- Rear wall system: $315-425
- Crowson system: $1,800-2,600
- Main electronics: $8,650-10,700
- Speakers (including isolation): $8,270-10,870
- Screen/Projector: $32,000-34,000
- Acoustic treatment: $3,500-7,500
- Seating: $4,000-8,000
- **Total: ~$68,676-85,044**

**Rev 4.1 Cost Impact:**
- Front subs: +$145 (larger enclosures, integrated covers)
- Rear subs: +$330 (larger enclosures, integrated covers)
- Stage platform: +$13 (larger corner pockets)
- Eliminated: -$220 (separate stage front AT panels)
- **Net increase: +$268** (improved driver protection and professional appearance)

**Rev 5.0 Cost Impact:**
- Atmos speakers: +$880-1,180 (DIYSG Volt-10 vs. DIY Eminence build)
- Benefit: Guaranteed reference capability (107-108 dB) vs. marginal performance (104-105 dB)
- Result: Eliminates weak link in reference-level system, proper integration across all channels

**Notes:**
- Prices are estimates based on current market (2024-2025)
- Actual costs in 2027 may vary
- Does not include: Tools, consumables (paint, caulk beyond listed), HVAC modifications, electrical work, general room construction
- Professional calibration: $500-1,500 additional
- PURIFI amplification adds ~$2,200 over original NC502MP budget but provides critical silent operation and proper headroom
- Rev 4.1 adds 3" recessed driver mounting with integrated AT covers for +$268 net cost (improved protection and aesthetics)
- Rev 5.0 upgrades Atmos to DIYSG Volt-10 for +$880-1,180 (eliminates performance weak link, ensures reference capability)

